{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.30",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 30 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:1",
      "text": "The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, the revelation: the man says to Ithiel, to Ithiel and Ucal:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:2",
      "text": "“ Surely I am the most ignorant man, and don’t have a man’s understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:3",
      "text": "I have not learned wisdom, neither do I have the knowledge of the Holy One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:4",
      "text": "Who has ascended up into heaven, and descended? Who has gathered the wind in his fists? Who has bound the waters in his garment? Who has established all the ends of the earth? What is his name, and what is his son ’s name, if you know?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:5",
      "text": "“ Every word of God is flawless. He is a shield to those who take refuge in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:6",
      "text": "Don’t you add to his words, lest he reprove you, and you be found a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:7",
      "text": "“ Two things I have asked of you. Don’t deny me before I die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:8",
      "text": "Remove far from me falsehood and lies. Give me neither poverty nor riches. Feed me with the food that is needful for me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:9",
      "text": "lest I be full, deny you, and say, ‘ Who is Yahweh?’ or lest I be poor, and steal, and so dishonor the name of my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:10",
      "text": "“Don’t slander a servant to his master, lest he curse you, and you be held guilty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:11",
      "text": "There is a generation that curses their father, and doesn’t bless their mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:12",
      "text": "There is a generation that is pure in their own eyes, yet are not washed from their filthiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:13",
      "text": "There is a generation, oh how lofty are their eyes! Their eyelids are lifted up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:14",
      "text": "There is a generation whose teeth are like swords, and their jaws like knives, to devour the poor from the earth, and the needy from among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:15",
      "text": "“ The leech has two daughters: ‘ Give, give.’ “There are three things that are never satisfied; four that don’t say, ‘ Enough!’:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:16",
      "text": "Sheol, the barren womb, the earth that is not satisfied with water, and the fire that doesn’t say, ‘ Enough!’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:17",
      "text": "“ The eye that mocks at his father, and scorns obedience to his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, the young eagles shall eat it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:18",
      "text": "“ There are three things which are too amazing for me, four which I don’t understand:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:19",
      "text": "The way of an eagle in the air, the way of a serpent on a rock, the way of a ship in the middle of the sea, and the way of a man with a maiden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:20",
      "text": "“ So is the way of an adulterous woman: She eats and wipes her mouth, and says, ‘ I have done nothing wrong.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:21",
      "text": "“ For three things the earth trembles, and under four, it can ’t bear up:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:22",
      "text": "For a servant when he is king, a fool when he is filled with food,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:23",
      "text": "for an unloved woman when she is married, and a servant who is heir to her mistress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:24",
      "text": "“ There are four things which are little on the earth, but they are exceedingly wise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:25",
      "text": "The ants are not a strong people, yet they provide their food in the summer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:26",
      "text": "The hyraxes are but a feeble folk, yet make they their houses in the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:27",
      "text": "The locusts have no king, yet they advance in ranks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:28",
      "text": "You can catch a lizard with your hands, yet it is in kings ’ palaces.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:29",
      "text": "“ There are three things which are stately in their march, four which are stately in going:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:30",
      "text": "The lion, which is mightiest among animals, and doesn’t turn away for any;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:31",
      "text": "the greyhound; the male goat; and the king against whom there is no rising up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:32",
      "text": "“If you have done foolishly in lifting up yourself, or if you have thought evil, put your hand over your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.30.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:33",
      "text": "For as the churning of milk produces butter, and the wringing of the nose produces blood, so the forcing of wrath produces strife.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
